At the time of the Spanish, Cuba was their base for the conquest of America.
Columbus called it the most beautiful place a human eye has ever seen.
Havana was once a storage or transit warehouse of treasures that the Spaniards had stolen from America and then transported to Europe.
And then came the American era.
The Hotel Nacional was founded at the end of the 20th century.
