Cuba also offers a marotte that is unique in the world and attracts railway lovers above all.
The sugar pipe from remote plantations brought steam and diesel-operated narrow-track railways to the sugar mills.
Its fleet has not been renewed for decades, so you can see clean and fully functioning locomotives, whose age-old comrades have been in the museum for a long time.
