The Viñales Valley in the west of the island is one of the most picturesque corners of Cuba.
The lush vegetation grows on lime floors.
The mogotas, limestone hills and rocks, rise steeply from the valley floor, in their cavities accumulated fertile soil, which is also covered in windy rock areas by dense vegetation.
This valley is where perhaps the best Cuban tobacco is grown.
In its final form you can meet him when you visit one of Havana’s cigar factories.
It may also seem interesting to some that the Chilean sequel to the TV series "Major Zeman" was filmed there.
Trinidad
An ancient city that was founded shortly after the Spanish colonized the island.
Glory and wealth brought her the trade of slaves and sugar.
The wealth was embodied in the beautiful beauty of the small town.
Spanish colonial architecture, strongly influenced by the later French settlers, has barely changed for four hundred years.
Trinidad, located between the sea and the Escambray Mountains, is such a remote place that there was no road connecting the area to the rest of the country in the 1950s.
This isolation contributed to the fact that it remained unnoticed.
Nothing was built there, but therefore nothing was torn down, everyone was happy that he had a roof over his head.
